NEW MEXICO LIFE INSURANCE COMPANY v. L. F. CORRIGAN. No. 5378. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Sept. 4, 1956. Owen B. Marrón, Albuquerque, N. M., for appellant. Rodey, Dickason, Sloan, Mims & Akin, Albuquerque, N. M., for appellee.

Before BRATTON, Chief Judge, and MURRAH and LEWIS, Circuit Judges.

Appeal dismissed pursuant to stipulation of the parties.
